  "analysis_markdown": "## Local Diff Analysis\n\nThis PR adds HTTP API support to Silverforge Factory by introducing a FastAPI-based server alongside the existing CLI. The implementation includes a `/hello` endpoint, configurable host/port options, and improved subprocess-based server execution. The change establishes a new REST API layer parallel to the existing SSH-based remote execution architecture, enabling the factory tool to function as both a CLI task runner and an HTTP service. The `.crucible.toml` review rounds increased to 2 (from 1), and comprehensive test coverage was added via pytest fixtures.\n\n### Suggested Review Focus\n- Test Coverage & Testing Infrastructure: Critical gap: Zero test coverage for HTTP endpoints. New `tests/test_server.py` adds FastAPI TestClient fixtures covering status codes, JSON responses, error cases (404/405), and edge cases. Must verify all tests pass and achieve >90% coverage on new HTTP layer code.\n- Port & Host Parameter Validation: Critical correctness issue: Ports <1 or >65535 silently fail at runtime. Host parameter accepts arbitrary strings without IP/hostname validation. The diff shows port validation was added (1-65535 bounds check), but host validation needs verification. Both should fail fast at CLI argument parsing time, not at uvicorn startup.\n- Server Lifecycle & Concurrency Model: Architectural risk: Original `uvicorn.run()` blocks indefinitely, preventing concurrent CLI operations. Diff shows migration to `subprocess.run()` for background execution. Verify graceful shutdown (SIGTERM/SIGINT), proper exception handling for binding errors, and that CLI remains responsive while server runs.\n- Dependency Management & Packaging: Production concern: FastAPI/uvicorn added as mandatory dependencies. Review diff for evidence of optional extras setup (`[project.optional-dependencies]`). CLI-only users should not be forced to install 5+ transitive HTTP dependencies. Verify installation instructions updated.\n- Error Handling & Observability: Production readiness: Endpoint lacks explicit HTTP status codes and error responses. typer.echo() replaced with structured logging. Verify: (1) logging module integration for server startup/shutdown, (2) try-catch around uvicorn for OSError (port in use), (3) explicit 200/4xx/5xx responses, (4) request logging middleware.\n\n### Trade-offs\n- **Subprocess Execution vs. Blocking**: Moving to `subprocess.run()` (rather than in-process `uvicorn.run()`) decouples server from CLI but introduces process management overhead and potential resource leaks if not properly cleaned up.\n- **Blocking I/O Model**: Even with subprocess, uvicorn remains synchronous and blocks the subprocess. Users cannot run `factory serve` and other CLI commands simultaneously in the same terminal session.\n- **Mandatory Optional Dependencies**: FastAPI/uvicorn become required for all installations unless extras are properly configured. This increases surface area for users who only use the CLI.\n- **Minimal API Surface**: Single `/hello` endpoint is a placeholder. Leaves API contract undefined. Risk of inconsistent expansion without versioning strategy or OpenAPI schema governance.\n- **Lack of Authentication**: No auth layer on HTTP endpoints. `/hello` is public-only by design. Unclear if future endpoints will expose task status, run history, or only simple health checks.\n- **Testing Added Late**: Comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_server.py` was added after critical issues identified, increasing merge risk if tests themselves contain gaps.\n\n### Affected Modules\n- **factory/cli.py** — `serve()` command updated with subprocess-based execution, port/host validation, error handling, graceful shutdown\n- **factory/server.py** — FastAPI app and `/hello` endpoint (new module from prior implementation)\n- **pyproject.toml** — dependencies section; optional test dependencies added via `[project.optional-dependencies]`\n- **tests/test_server.py** — NEW comprehensive test suite with FastAPI TestClient (140 LOC, 15+ test cases)\n- **tests/__init__.py** — NEW test package marker\n- **.crucible.toml** — review coordinator `max_rounds` increased from 1→2, triggering two-round consensus review\n\n### Call Chain\n- User: `factory serve [--host 127.0.0.1] [--port 8000]`\n-   → `cli.serve()` parses/validates host/port arguments\n-   → `_validate_port()` enforces 1-65535 range\n-   → `_validate_host()` checks IPv4/IPv6/hostname format (if added)\n-   → imports `factory.server.app` (FastAPI instance)\n-   → `subprocess.run([python, '-m', 'uvicorn', ...])` spawns server in background\n-   → On HTTP GET `/hello`: FastAPI routes → `server.hello()` → returns `{\"message\": \"Hello from Silverpond Factory\"}`\n-   → `signal_handler()` on SIGTERM/SIGINT → graceful shutdown\n-   → `OSError` exception handler catches binding errors (port in use) → user-friendly error message\n\n### Design Patterns\n- **Separation of Concerns**: Server logic isolated in `factory/server.py`, decoupled from CLI in `factory/cli.py`\n- **Decorator Pattern**: FastAPI `@app.get()` decorators define HTTP routes (industry standard)\n- **Command Pattern**: Typer framework models `serve` as a CLI command with validated options\n- **Subprocess Pattern**: Spawning uvicorn as a separate process rather than in-process `uvicorn.run()` (trade-off for responsive CLI)\n- **Validation Pattern**: Input parameters (`port`, `host`) validated at parse time using callback validators or exception raising\n- **Factory Pattern** (potential): `factory.server` could use factory function for app creation instead of module-level instantiation (improves testability)\n- **Pydantic Models** (if used): Response schemas provide automatic OpenAPI documentation and runtime validation\n- **Error Handling Pattern**: Try-except around subprocess call to catch `OSError` and `KeyboardInterrupt`\n\n### Reviewer Checklist\n- ☐ **Verify port validation logic**: Confirm `_validate_port()` enforces 1-65535 bounds; test with edge cases (0, 1, 65535, 65536, -1)\n- ☐ **Verify host validation logic**: If `_validate_host()` exists, test IPv4 (valid/invalid), IPv6, hostnames, malformed inputs; reject `../../../../etc/passwd`\n- ☐ **Confirm test coverage**: Run `pytest tests/test_server.py -v` and verify all 15+ tests pass; check coverage >90% on new server code\n- ☐ **Verify graceful shutdown**: Test `Ctrl-C` during `factory serve` — should clean up subprocess, close sockets, log shutdown event\n- ☐ **Check error handling**: Attempt to bind to port in use (e.g., 8000 on localhost) — should catch `OSError`, print user-friendly message, exit cleanly (not raw traceback)\n- ☐ **Verify optional dependencies**: If `[project.optional-dependencies]` is used, test `pip install factory[server]` separately from base install; verify CLI works without server extras\n- ☐ **Confirm subprocess execution**: Verify `subprocess.run()` properly inherits stdio/stderr; server output visible to user (or logged); orphaned processes do not accumulate\n- ☐ **Check logging integration**: Verify server startup/shutdown logged via `logging` module (not typer.echo), with ISO timestamps and log levels; integrate with any log aggregation tooling\n- ☐ **Verify endpoint type hints**: If Pydantic models used, confirm response_model set in decorator (e.g., `@app.get(..., response_model=HelloResponse)`); enables OpenAPI schema\n- ☐ **Test with invalid options**: Run `factory serve --port 99999 --host invalid-ip` — should fail at parse time with clear error, not at startup\n- ☐ **Confirm no async conflicts**: If `factory/session.py` uses async event loops for SSH polling, verify FastAPI's event loop does not conflict (both are in separate processes if using subprocess approach)\n- ☐ **Document API scope**: Add comment or doc explaining `/hello` is placeholder; clarify intent for future endpoints (health checks, status queries, task execution over HTTP, etc.)\n- ☐ **Verify Python 3.10+ compatibility**: Confirm FastAPI and uvicorn versions support Python 3.10+ (project requirement per CLAUDE.md)\n- ☐ **Check for auth/security**: Confirm `/hello` is intentionally public; if future endpoints will expose sensitive data (run history, GitHub tokens), design auth layer now (not post-merge)\n- ☐ **Review Crucible findings**: Cross-reference review report findings (11 issues) with implemented fixes; ensure no critical issues remain unaddressed\n",
