        "body": "**Host parameter accepts arbitrary strings without validation**\n\nThe host parameter is declared as a simple string option with no validation. Users can pass invalid values like ';;;;', '../../../etc/passwd', '256.256.256.256', or malformed input that will silently fail at uvicorn startup time (not at CLI parse time). This violates the principle of fail-fast validation at argument parsing and provides poor user experience.\n\nRaised by: claude-code\n\nSuggested fix: Add a validation function using ipaddress module and regex for hostnames. Use Typer's callback parameter or raise typer.BadParameter() to fail at parse time: `def _validate_host(value: str) -> str: ...` and pass as `callback=_validate_host` to typer.Option().",
