        "body": "**Exception handling incomplete; OSError from binding failures won't be caught**\n\nThe exception handler catches KeyboardInterrupt and subprocess.CalledProcessError, but if uvicorn fails to bind (e.g., port already in use, permission denied, invalid host), the OSError will be raised inside the subprocess and communicated via CalledProcessError. However, the error message from CalledProcessError may not be user-friendly. If the subprocess itself crashes with an unhandled OSError, it will exit with a non-zero code, triggering CalledProcessError, but the original error context is lost.\n\nRaised by: claude-code\n\nSuggested fix: Capture stderr from subprocess.run() and check for common error patterns. E.g., if 'Address already in use' is detected, suggest using a different port. Add `capture_output=True, text=True` to subprocess.run() and examine result.stderr.",
